properties.name: Kenny Chesney Concert
properties.description: Posted by Makaio50 455 N. 10th Street, Omaha, NE 68101 Ughh... did you say Uncle Cracker!!! was coming to this concert!!! I\'m glad there\'s a possible tornado outside right now because otherwise I\'d leave! Country concert artists work hard, put on a good show, and completely fulfill the patriotic stereotypes of the genre (besides the f-ing Dixy Chicks). Other than acting like a mouse in a swiss watchmakers tool shed I enjoyed the concert in a most spectacular way. I was glad to be there in support of Ashley... and to further the cause of country music in America... but mostly Ashley!

properties.name: Matt's Birthplace
properties.description: Posted by Makaio50Erling Berquist Strategic Hospital This is where Matthew Thomas Edward McCrary was born. He was prompty walloped on the butt, had his feet smudged with ink and applied to stationary paper, and was made to wear a one-sie, bracelet, and cap which were completely removed from the fashionable norms of the time (Little better were his clothes for the next 15 years which were the fashionable norms of the time.) The records of this foul behavior were later destroyed subsequencing the invent of the personal computer. Surprisingly in excellent health, he had not made a trip to the doctor\'s in years... so the hospital threw his papers in the recycling bin. At least some good came of this terrible ordeal.

properties.name: The exact spot where Matt told Ashley he loved her
properties.description: Posted by Makaio5013204 S. 29th St. Bellevue, NE 68123From the journal: "[...] Last Thursday night I told Ashley I loved her. I\'d told her something to that effect earlier in the week like, \'I think I love you,\' but that was an inkling & this was a decleration - something I was sure of. We\'d gone to the playground of Leonard Lawrence where I\'d gone to Elementary School. Everything seemed very comfortable - very right that night. It was that night I discovered that kissing her would never grow old as it does sometimes with your significant other. At about 10:50pm we got up to leave and what seemed like minutes later it was 12:30am. It was in this time where it felt like the meteor hit us and sent us flying to the moon. That almost describes the sensation except less oxygen. Actually it was more like too much oxygen - like runners high when I finally realised & discovered that I love this girl in my arms who loves me so much in return.
